summary: The All-Nighter
title: The All-Nighter
body:
I’ve wanted to get into writing for awhile, but I never really ran with it. Thankfully, that changed today. I present to you my first ever attempt at dabbling in fan-fic. Please enjoy!

 ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ 

Tony stood from his work bench and rolled his stiff shoulders, letting out a long sigh. He looked up from the helmet he was repairing for the first time in hours.

His eyes swept the lab until his gaze landed on the ceiling. “Fri, what time is it?”

“Way past your bedtime, Boss.” Tony rolled his eyes.

“Very funny, Fri, but seriously, what time is it?”

“2:13 in the morning.” Tony groaned. 

“You really should get some sleep.” Tony groaned louder.

After asking FRIDAY to turn of all of the lights, computers, and various other bits of tech whirring throughout the lab, Tony made his way to the elevator. When he stepped into the common room, he was surprised to find a heated game of Mario Kart displayed on the TV. He approached the couch from behind, careful to not give himself away with heavy footsteps.

He found Peter wrapped head to toe in a Spiderman blanket with only his face and his hands peering out so he could continue playing his game. He muttered a curse under his breath when another driver passed him on the final lap.

“Hey, Pete.” Tony spoke softly so as not to startle the enthralled teen. Peter’s spidey senses, however, decided to turn a whisper into a shout. Peter jumped so high into the air he nearly wound up on the ceiling. The wii remote skidded across the floor.

“U-uh, hi, Mr. St-stark.” The guilt weighed heavy on Peter’s face. “Sorry for showing up here uninvited. It’s just that, well, I couldn’t sleep, and I didn’t want to disturb Aunt May because she had a really long shift today. She’s just so tired all the time and needs her sleep more than I do and-” Peter paused to breathe and glanced up at the face of his mentor. “You aren’t mad?”

The kid’s word pulled at Tony’s heartstrings. How could he ever be mad at him? Sure, he was far from pleased with whoever or whatever was keeping the kid up at night, but if anything, he was touched that Peter came to him.

Tony shook his head and smiled. “Do you want to talk, Underoos? I can make some hot chocolate.”

The light returned to the boy’s eyes as he nodded eagerly and reassembled his fleece cocoon.

When Tony returned with two steaming mugs, the pair sat on the sofa and talked until the sun filtered in through the windows. As the flow of thoughts slowed, Peter’s head fell on Tony’s chest, and the man brushed back his curls. Before long, they both fell soundly asleep.

summary: Ironstrange Kisses #27 - Because We Are Hiding
title: Ironstrange Kisses #27 - Because We Are Hiding
body:
Tony pulls Stephen into a supply closet. Together, they stumble until Stephen leans on the wall. “Really?” Stephen asks. “Here?”

“Why not?”

“We’re at the kid’s high school!”

“It’s kind of fun, right? Sneaking around like teenagers…”

“If we get caught, Peter will kill us..”

“Luckily, you’re a magic man,” Tony says against those wonderful lips. And when he kisses them, Stephen is too weak to protest. He presses up against Tony, wedged between the love of his life and a wall.

Peter will never be any the wiser.

summary: Ironstrange Kisses #26 - Because It Doesn’t Hurt
title: Ironstrange Kisses #26 - Because It Doesn’t Hurt
body:
Kissing had never meant much to Tony in the past, but now, with the man he is going to marry, it means everything. Kissing used to be painful…

The kisses in his past had meant nothing. They were shallow things with no love and a feigned sort of passion. They hurt for how fake they were. Either that, or they were too passionate, compensating for all that they really lacked.

Kissing was always temporary and it did not last.

Kissing with Stephen though, always takes away the pain. It is eternal and never temporary. It is bliss.

“What are you staring at me like that for?” Stephen asks, as they sit together in Stephen’s bed. They’ve yet to figure out proper living arrangements that will cater to both of their lives, but they are doing well enough with what they have. When you have a man who can portal, there’s not that much to worry about. “Tony…”

“I want to kiss you.”

Stephen laughs, the sound adorable. “Well, you do have my permission.”

The kiss is bliss.

summary:
I've been thinking, and you know there are certain parallels between Hulk and Ultron. 
See, both were made, against better...
body:
I’ve been thinking, and you know there are certain parallels between Hulk and Ultron.

See, both were made, against better judgment, by men who were just looking to keep the world safe. Maybe misguided, but you know what they say about good intentions.

I’ve also noticed a reluctance to blame Bruce for the actions of the Hulk, especially while he was under the control of Wanda’s magic.

So why won’t ya’ll give Tony the same respect?
